Gusau – National Commission for Refugees, Migrants and Internally Displaced Persons (NCFRMIDP), has donated relief items worth millions of naira to the victims of recent armed attacks in Zurmi, Maradun and Shinkafi local government areas in Zamfara State. Presenting the relief items to Atiku Abubakar, the Emir of Zurmi on Sunday, Hajiya Sadiya Faruk, the federal commissioner, NCFRMIDP, described the incident as worrisome and barbaric. According to her, the items donated by the commission to victims of Birane attack in Zurmi Emirate include 67 bags of rice, 67 100kg bags of beans, 67 100kg bags of Millet, 67 100kg bags of maize, 15 cartons of vegetable oil, 15 cartons of salt, 1000 marts, 115 yards of textile materials and N1 million cash. At Moriki Emirate, she donated assorted drugs, mosquito nets, soap, and clothing worth millions of naira to the families of those who lost their loved ones as a result of armed attack in the area. She also donated 140 sewing machines, 67 100kg bags of millet, 67 100kg bags of maize, 67 100kg bags of beans, 61 watering cans, 120 goats and sheep, among others to the IDPs in Shinkafi and Maradun emirates. “The gesture was in line of the Federal Government’s effort to eradicate the suffering the IDPs were facing and to empower them to have a sense of belonging,” she said. She appealed for judicious distribution of the items to the beneficiaries, stressing that the items were mainly for victims of armed bandits attacks not for personal use. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.